  <abstract>Image of three men smiling and applauding, most likely Pro-Constantine Greeks attending a dinner at the Granit Club at the Westbury Hotel. Verso reads: "Pro-Constantine Greeks attending the dinner at the Granite club screamed at the picketers across the street as they left the dinner.  Here are 2 of them raising spread-fingered hands in the worst of all Greek curses, which means, literally, "may you burn in hell forever".  This sign was translated for [reporter] John Gault by a Greek."</abstract>
